\[
\text{Area} = \text{length} \times \text{width}
\]

\[
3,000 = \text{length} \times 100 \implies \text{length} = \frac{3,000}{100} = 30 \text{ feet}
\]

Thus, the length of the other side is **30 feet**, corresponding to option A.

Answer: A
